# CONTRIBUTING.md

## Development Workflow

1. Check `AGENT_RULES.md`.
2. Check `ROADMAP.md`.
3. Check `ARCHITECTURE.md`.
4. Create a branch when making code changes.
5. Make focused changes.
6. Run relevant tests.
7. Commit with a descriptive message.
8. Open pull request when appropriate.
9. Review changed files.
10. Merge only after validation.

## Branch Naming

Use:

```text
feature/name
fix/name
refactor/name
docs/name
test/name
chore/name
```

Examples:

```text
feature/user-dashboard
fix/login-error
refactor/api-services
docs/update-readme
test/add-api-tests
chore/update-config
```

## Commit Message Rules

Good:

```text
Add user dashboard layout
Fix API validation error
Update deployment documentation
Add tests for input validation
```

Bad:

```text
fix
stuff
changes
update
latest
```

## Pull Request Requirements

Every pull request should explain:
- what changed
- why it changed
- files affected
- testing performed
- risks
- deployment impact
- rollback plan if relevant

## Code Review Checklist

- [ ] Scope is focused
- [ ] No unrelated files changed
- [ ] No secrets exposed
- [ ] Tests/build checked
- [ ] Documentation updated if needed
- [ ] Architecture respected
- [ ] Security impact reviewed
- [ ] Deployment impact reviewed
